                    <note>
                        <date type="foundation" notBefore="1350" notAfter="1449">Possibly around mid-14th century.</date>
                        <ab type="history">Dabr. According to the local tradition, the first church was built in the 12th century.
                            Before,  the area is said to have been occupied by the 'people who came from Israel' and by Kalaw-Balaw.
                            The present church is said to have been built some 120 years ago. Some archaeological traces of early settlements
                            were discovered in the area around the church. 
                        </ab>
                        <ab type="tabot">
                            <measure quantity="2">4</measure> four main  tābots,                              
                             <persName ref="PRS6819Mary" type="tabot">Mary</persName>. 
                            <persName ref="PRS1906Ananyao" type="tabot">ʾAnānyā</persName>, 
                            <persName ref="PRS6298Libanos" type="tabot">Libānos</persName>, 
                            and of the three Patriarchs <persName ref="PRS5650Jacob" type="tabot">Jacob</persName>
                            <persName ref="PRS1269Abraham" type="tabot">Abreham</persName>, and 
                            <persName ref="PRS5578Isaac" type="tabot">Isaac</persName>.
                        </ab>
                        
                        <ab type="description">33 manuscripts were inventarized on <date>30 March 2024</date>
                            by Getnet Desta, Amanuel Abrha, Hailay Atsbha (Department of Archaeology and Heritage Management, 
                            Adigrat University), and Hagos Gebremariam (Department of Sociology, Adigrat University).</ab>
